article.description: — Zach Cooks had a season-high 25 points as NJIT topped Stony Brook 74-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Cooks scores 25 to lead NJIT over Stony Brook 74-65
article.linkText: Cooks scores 25 to lead NJIT over Stony Brook 74-65
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- — Zach Cooks had a season-high 25 points as NJIT topped Stony Brook 74-65 on Saturday. Miles Coleman had 12 points for NJIT (5-6, 4-5 America East Conference). Antwuan Butler added 10 points. Jaden Sayles scored a career-high 32 points and had seven rebounds for the Seawolves (6-7, 4-3). Juan Felix Rodriguez added 14 points and six assists. Mouhamadou Gueye had 11 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
